I would give this place no stars if I could.  First, let’s start with the food: greasy, overcooked and unseasoned. I ordered the chicken fajita wrap and it was poorly made. There was oil literally dripping from the wrap. The pieces of meat and vegetables were chopped too largely so there wasn’t an even mix of all the ingredients in each bite. I would take one bite and it was all green peppers. Another bite and it’s all avocado. The chicken was grilled but not at all seasoned. It didn’t even taste like they added salt and pepper to the meat.  My sister ordered the Neptune sampler and the “buffalo” wings were not even spicy. They were saltier than anything. The wings were so over fried that it cut up the top of her mouth. The chicken tenders were also kind of dry.  Let’s move on to the service: mediocre. At first the service was ok. Our server took our order quickly and we got the food in a decent amount of time. But when it was time to go we had to wait SO long to get the check, even though there were not that many other customers and our server was just standing around. After we finally got the check, we had another long wait before someone came to take our cards. Our server finally came and got the check and our cards, then an old man returned them to us. He literally stood over us watching us as we signed the receipts. And it made me VERY uncomfortable that we had to wait so long to get our check and pay but then he stood over us waiting for us to sign. I asked him for a to-go box and he kind of just looked at me like he didn’t understand what I was saying.  As a black woman I would never come back to this diner again. The food was bad and the service was bad. There is no sense of hospitality and customer service.

Food was dripping with grease; I needed extra napkins. Service is ABSURDLY slow. There were between 3-4 tables the whole time I was there so it's not that they're busy. I overheard another table comment on how they wonder why they are being singled out for having to wait so long just to order their food when the place was obviously not busy; I told them that I, too, had waited 20 minutes after I received my order for the waitress even to check on me, at which point my drink had been empty almost the whole time. I didn't even eat a decent bit of the food I ordered because it was so greasy. I see nothing terribly redeeming about this place based on my only visit, and don't plan to return.  Free WiFi.
